20He%20is%20a%20representative%20of%20a%20viewpoint%20which%20may%20not%20be%20consistent%20with%20the%20views%20of%20the%20government.%20Care%20must%20be%20taken%20not%20to%20exclude%20such%20voices%20from%20the%20parliament%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20court%20said%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fnews%2Fnational%2Fwe-have-lost-our-sense-of-humour-in-public-life-cji-observes-in-raghav-chadha-indefinite-suspension-case-hearing%2Farticle67476797.ece%5C%22%3Eaccording%20to%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Hindu%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EA%20three-judge%20bench%20of%20Chief%20Justice%20D.Y.%20Chandrachud%2C%20Justice%20J.B.%20Pardiwala%2C%20and%20Justice%20Manoj%20Mishra%20on%20Monday%2C%20October%2030%2C%20said%20that%20indefinite%20suspension%20of%20an%20MP%20from%20the%20House%20undermines%20the%20right%20of%20people%20to%20be%20represented.%C2%A0They%20said%20the%20principle%20of%20proportionality%20should%20be%20kept%20in%20mind%20in%20such%20cases.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EChadha%20was%20suspended%20from%20the%20House%20starting%20August%2011%20for%20an%20indefinite%20period%20until%20the%20Privileges%20Committee%2C%20which%20is%20probing%20the%20matter%2C%20submits%20its%20report.%20His%20suspension%20came%20after%20five%20Rajya%20Sabha%20MPs%20accused%20Chadha%20of%20mentioning%20their%20names%20without%20their%20consent%20in%20the%20motion%20that%20sought%20a%20select%20committee%20to%20examine%20the%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fdelhi-services-bill-rajya-sabha-arvind-kejriwal-centre-ias-officer-amit-shah%5C%22%3EGovernment%20of%20National%20Capital%20Territory%20of%20Delhi%20(Amendment)%20Bill%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%202023.%20S.%20Phangnon%20Konyak%2C%20Narhari%20Amin%2C%20and%20Sudhanshu%20Trivedi%20of%20the%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party%20(BJP)%3B%20M.%20Thambidurai%20of%20the%20All%20India%20Anna%20Dravida%20Munnetra%20Kazhagam%20(AIADMK)%3B%20and%20Sasmit%20Patra%20of%20the%20Biju%20Janata%20Dal%20(BJD)%20levelled%20the%20allegation%20against%20the%20AAP%20MP.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20court%20said%20it%20doubted%20if%20Chadha%E2%80%99s%20conduct%20amounted%20to%20a%20breach%20of%20parliamentary%20privilege.%20Speaking%20for%20the%20Bench%2C%20the%20CJI%20said%20consent%20of%20fellow%20MPs%20is%20necessary%20at%20the%20stage%20of%20appointing%20them%20to%20a%20committee.%20While%20acknowledging%20the%20charge%20against%20Chadha%2C%20the%20CJI%20wondered%20if%20Chadha%E2%80%99s%20act%20of%20not%20informing%20fellow%20MPs%20whom%20he%20included%20in%20his%20proposal%20for%20the%20said%20committee%20amounted%20to%20a%20violation%20of%20the%20rules.%20He%20also%20pointed%20out%20that%20MPs%20are%20only%20suspended%20for%20the%20remainder%20of%20a%20particular%20session%20in%20the%20case%20of%20disruptions%2C%20wondering%20whether%20allegations%20against%20Chadha%20warrant%20an%20indefinite%20suspension.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIs%20this%20worse%20than%20the%20disruption%20of%20proceedings%3F%20Is%20this%20really%20on%20a%20higher%20level%3F%20A%20person%20who%20disrupts%20the%20House%20is%20excluded%20for%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20session.%20In%20this%20case%20alleged%20infraction%20is%20that%20he%20didn%E2%80%99t%20verify.%20Some%20proportionality%20is%20now%20an%20invented%20part%20of%20our%20jurisprudence%2C%E2%80%9D%20CJI%20told%20Attorney%20General%20for%20India%20R.%20Venkataramani%2C%20who%20represented%20the%20Rajya%20Sabha%20chairman%20and%20secretariat%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livelaw.in%2Ftop-stories%2Fsupreme-court-expresses-concerns-at-indefinite-suspension-of-aap-mp-raghav-chadha-from-rajya-sabha-241192%3Finfinitescroll%3D1%5C%22%3Eaccording%20to%20%3Cem%3ELivelaw%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20CJI%20then%20goes%20on%20to%20say%2C%20%E2%80%9CThat%20we%20have%20lost%20our%20sense%20of%20humour%20in%20public%20life%20is%20a%20separate%20thing%20altogether%E2%80%A6%20What%20he%20obviously%20meant%20by%20%E2%80%98sending%20birthday%20invitation%20cards%E2%80%99%20is%20that%20the%20members%20could%20either%20come%20or%20not%20come%E2%80%A6%20Does%20that%20really%2C%20really%20reduce%20the%20dignity%20of%20the%20House%20and%20cause%20a%20breach%20of%20privilege%3F%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EChadha%E2%80%99s%20counsel%2C%20Rakesh%20Dwivedi%2C%20told%20the%20court%20that%20the%20member%20had%20already%20tendered%20his%20apology%20and%20conveyed%20the%20same%20to%20the%20Rajya%20Sabha%20chairman.%20Therefore%2C%20Dwivedi%20said%2C%20the%20indefinite%20suspension%20is%20%E2%80%9Cpatently%20illegal%20and%20violative%20of%20the%20law%20and%20constitution%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHe%20also%20informed%20the%20court%20that%20there%20have%20been%2011%20instances%20in%20the%20last%2075%20years%20where%20MPs%20included%20the%20names%20of%20their%20fellow%20MPs%20who%20were%20unwilling%20to%20be%20part%20of%20motions.%20And%2C%20he%20went%20on%20to%20add%20that%20those%20names%20were%20merely%20dropped%20without%20slapping%20a%20suspension%20order%20against%20the%20MPs%20in%20question.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20court%20asked%20whether%20the%20Rajya%20Sabha%20chairman%20would%20accept%20if%20Chadha%20was%20%E2%80%9Cready%20and%20willing%E2%80%9D%20to%20apologise.%20Venkataramani%20then%20said%20the%20Rajya%20Sabha%20chairperson%20had%20suspended%20Chadha%20pending%20the%20inquiry%20by%20the%20Privileges%20Committee%20following%20a%20resolution%20passed%20by%20the%20House%20itself.%C2%A0The%20matter%20will%20be%20next%20heard%20on%20November%203.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1698764453000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F09%2F01182007%2FRadghav-Chadha.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fdont-exclude-oppositions-voice-from-parliament-says-sc-on-raghav-chadhas-suspension-from-rs%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Chief%20Justice%20D.Y.%20Chandrachud%20said%20indefinite%20suspension%20of%20an%20MP%20from%20the%20House%20undermines%20the%20right%20of%2